@startuml
scale 1400 width
title VBoxManage clipboard serve - host-to-guest data path
hide empty description
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 96

[*] --> Setup : serve starts
Setup : Get IClipboard and IHostClipboard
Setup : Register event listener
Setup --> ServeLoop
Setup --> Failed : setup error

state ServeLoop {
  [*] --> Waiting
  Waiting : Common wait state
  Waiting : waits for event, timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Stopping : timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Dispatch : event received

  Dispatch : Decode VBoxEventType
  Dispatch --> DataChangedEvent : DataChanged
  Dispatch --> TransferEvent : Transfer
  Dispatch --> OtherEvent : SourceChanged, FormatChanged,\nDataRequested, Error or ModeChanged

  DataChangedEvent : Read IClipboardItem source, MIME and buffer
  DataChangedEvent --> ValidateHostData : source == Host
  DataChangedEvent --> Continue : source != Host

  ValidateHostData : Require supported MIME type
  ValidateHostData : Require non-empty payload
  ValidateHostData --> WriteHostDataToGuest : valid host-owned data
  ValidateHostData --> Continue : unsupported or empty

  WriteHostDataToGuest : IClipboard::WriteDataRaw(Copy, Host, mime, bytes)
  WriteHostDataToGuest : Store host-owned Main clipboard item
  WriteHostDataToGuest : Report formats to the guest service
  WriteHostDataToGuest --> Continue : success
  WriteHostDataToGuest --> FailedEvent : COM error

  TransferEvent : Read transfer, state, interaction and path
  TransferEvent --> HostFileOffer : direction == ToGuest\nstate == Added or Interaction
  TransferEvent --> TransferProgress : direction == ToGuest\nstate update
  TransferEvent --> Continue : direction != ToGuest

  HostFileOffer : IClipboardTransfer::Roots/List/Query
  HostFileOffer : approve() or deny(reason)
  HostFileOffer --> Continue : approved, denied or pending

  TransferProgress : Track InProgress, Completed,\nCanceled, Failed or Removed
  TransferProgress --> Continue

  OtherEvent : Handled by another focused diagram
  OtherEvent --> Continue

  Continue --> Waiting
  FailedEvent : Print serve failure
  FailedEvent --> Stopping
}

ServeLoop --> Cleanup : stopped
Failed --> Cleanup
Cleanup : IHostClipboard::Clear()
Cleanup : Unregister listener
Cleanup : Uninstall signal handler
Cleanup --> [*]

note right of WriteHostDataToGuest
  This is the regular generic IClipboard path.
  The data source remains Host, so the guest can
  consume the item through the Shared Clipboard service.

  This path is separate from IHostClipboard, which is
  only used for native host clipboard publication.
end note

note right of HostFileOffer
  Host-to-guest file offers are represented by
  IClipboardTransfer(ToGuest). Local sourcePaths,
  such as /home/user/report.txt, configure the
  producer side only. The guest sees transfer roots,
  such as report.txt. Multiple selected files are
  roots in one transfer. Recursive directory listing
  is the default; NoRecursion opts out.
end note

@enduml
' EOF
